{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"78ac6c0b-a716-4725-8baf-10a70f76f1e2","content":"No existing files found. Since this is a guidance request rather than a modification to existing code, here's how to convert your page:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only structural change** is adding the `xmlns:vm` namespace import and the `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` attribute. All `{Binding …}` expressions stay the same — the XAML compiler now resolves them at build time.\n\n### 2. Catching binding errors at build time\n\nWith `x:DataType` in place, binding errors (e.g. `{Binding Themee}`) become **compiler errors** automatically — no extra flags needed.\n\nTo make warnings fail the build too, add to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <WarningsAsErrors>XC0045;XC0022</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `XC0045` | Property not found on the specified `x:DataType` |\n| `XC0022` | Type mismatch between binding source and target |\n\n### 3. Opting out for dynamic scenarios\n\nIf a specific binding must stay interpreted (e.g. binding to a `DataTemplate` item), use:\n\n```xml\n<Label Text=\"{Binding Path=Name, x:DataType=x:Null}\" />\n```\n\nThis disables compiled bindings for that single expression.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"535cd3e3-7e5b-4a41-9107-04c880564b06","outputTokens":620,"requestId":"110E:19B167:BFBB50:DFAC25:69FE84FF"},"id":"33ea4163-8940-42a1-a9b4-84af831df9cc","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:51:23.893Z","parentId":"3682a3f4-3652-4442-8311-8c29b024be65"}
